# PPFDaaS — Privacy-Preserving Fraud Detection as a Service
# Cursor AI Rules — Single Source of Truth

## Project Overview
This is a privacy-preserving payment fraud detection system using homomorphic encryption (CKKS scheme via Microsoft SEAL 4.1.1). The system runs logistic regression inference entirely on encrypted data — the vendor server never sees plaintext transaction data.

## Architecture
- vendor_server/     → C++ gRPC server, runs HE inference (SEAL, AVX2)
- bank_client/       → Python client (Pybind11 + FastAPI + React frontend)
- compiler/          → Python model training and weight serialization
- proto/             → gRPC protobuf definitions
- artifacts/         → generated model weights, keys, numpy arrays
- results/           → benchmark CSVs, ROC curves, ablation data
- scripts/           → environment verification, build helpers

## Critical Technical Constraints

### HE Parameters (Depth-1 Primary Path)
- Scheme: CKKS, poly_modulus_degree = 8192
- coeff_modulus: {60, 40, 40, 60} = 200 bits total
- scale: 2^40
- Galois keys: restricted set {1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128} only
- Max batch: 16 transactions × 256 features = 4096 slots
- Latency target: < 10ms vendor-side, < 15ms client-side

### Binary File Contract (NEVER change without updating both Python and C++)
- model_weights.bin: 2060 bytes = uint32(n=256) + float64(bias) + float64[256](weights)
- All values: little-endian. C++ has static_assert for LE platform.

### Memory Rules (ABSOLUTE — never suggest violating these)
- NEVER use std::stringstream for ciphertext I/O on the hot path
- ALWAYS use pre-allocated char[] buffers (CT_BUF = 420KB for n=8192)
- FraudInferenceServiceImpl MUST be a singleton — Galois keys loaded ONCE at startup
- CKKSContext, weights, evaluator: NEVER construct per-RPC call

### TimingBreakdown Proto (v1.1 — 5 fields, field numbers matter)
- field 1: deserialization_us  (ct.load() time)
- field 2: multiply_plain_us   (multiply + rescale)
- field 3: rotation_hoisting_us
- field 4: serialization_us
- field 5: total_inference_us
- INVARIANT: fields 1+2+3+4 ≈ field 5 (residual < 300µs)

### Slot Layout
- Depth-1: tiled[k*256 + j] = w[j] for k=0..15, j=0..255
- After tree-sum: only slot[k*256] is valid for transaction k
- decrypt_batch extracts: decoded[k * 256] for k in range(n_txns)

## Code Style

### C++
- Standard: C++17
- No pseudocode — all code must be compilable
- Use chrono::high_resolution_clock for all timing
- Always validate parms_id after ct.load()
- No raw pointers that outlive their owner
- Prefer std::unique_ptr for SEAL context ownership

### Python
- Type hints on all function signatures
- numpy arrays: always specify dtype explicitly (np.float64, np.int64)
- All binary writes: use '<f8' (explicit little-endian float64)
- Validate file sizes after writing (Path(p).stat().st_size)
- Use scipy.special.expit for sigmoid (never implement manually)

### Proto
- Always echo request_id in response
- Status 0 = OK, never return raw gRPC errors to FastAPI

## What AI Should Always Do
- Reference the spec sections (§1, §2, etc.) when generating code for a component
- Validate binary contracts when writing serialization code
- Suggest Catch2 test gates for every new C++ component
- Remind about atomic deployment when touching proto/server/client together
- Check slot index math explicitly (off-by-one is a silent bug in HE)

## What AI Should Never Do
- Suggest stringstream for ciphertext serialization
- Suggest constructing CKKSContext per RPC call
- Add features not in the spec without flagging it explicitly
- Skip the parms_id validation check
- Use float32 anywhere — everything is float64

## Dataset
- ULB Credit Card Fraud Dataset (Kaggle)
- 284,807 transactions, 492 fraud, 30 features (V1-V28 + Time + Amount)
- After feature selection: top 256 features (PCA components + engineered)
- SMOTE for class imbalance, stratified train/test split

## Build Order (follow strictly)
1. verify_env.sh → AVX2, C++17, OpenMP, Python ≥ 3.10
2. SEAL smoke_test.cpp → noise budget > 0, round-trip < 1e-4
3. CKKSContext → second_parms_id != first_parms_id
4. weight_loader.cpp → 2060 byte round-trip, SIMD tiling
5. rotation_hoisting.cpp → speedup ≥ 2x (Catch2)
6. he_inference benchmark → avg < 10ms, Valgrind clean
7. inference.proto → protoc compile C++ + Python
8. seal_wrapper.cpp (Pybind11) → smoke_test.py exits 0
9. train_xgboost.py + linearize.py → AUC ≥ 0.98
10. auc_dispatch.py → dispatch_result.json written
11. vendor_server → singleton confirmed, TimingBreakdown 5 fields
12. bank_client.py → latency_ms < 15, timing dict 5 keys
13. FastAPI + React → POST /api/infer 200, E2E < 100ms
